          <head>
            <note type="contents-note">This manuscript contains: The monk ʾAnān-Yeshūaʿ. "Illustrations of the Book of the Paradise," in four parts. In total, including sub-sections, this manuscript contains 5 items.</note>
            <listRelation type="Wright-BL-Taxonomy">
              <relation name="dcterms:type" ref="http://purl.org/dc/terms/type" active="https://bl.syriac.uk/ms/1080" passive="#lives-collect">
                <desc>Collected Lives</desc>
              </relation>
            </listRelation>
          </head>
          
          <msContents>
            <textLang mainLang="syr">Syriac</textLang>
            <msItem xml:id="a1" n="1" defective="true">
              <locus from="1a"/>
              <author>
                <persName xml:lang="en">The monk ʾAnān-Yeshūaʿ</persName>
              </author>
              <title xml:lang="en">"Illustrations of the Book of the Paradise," in
                        four parts. </title>
              <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܢܘܗܪ̈ܐ ܕܟܬܒܐ ܕܦܪܕܝܣܐ</rubric>
              <note>In reference to the author, see 
                  <persName>Thomas Maragensis</persName>, cited in
                <bibl>Assemani's Bibl. Or., t. iii., pars 1, pp. 144, 145<ref target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/7"/>
                </bibl>.</note>
              <note>It is written in the form of a dialogue between a teacher
                           (<foreign xml:lang="syr">ܣܒܐ</foreign> or <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܡ̇ܠܦܢܐ</foreign>) and his disciples
                (<foreign xml:lang="syr">ܐܚ̈ܐ</foreign>).</note>
              
              <msItem xml:id="b1" n="2" defective="true">
                <locus from="1a" to="12">Foll. 1a-12</locus>
                <title xml:lang="en">Part first, sections <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܠܓ ـــ
                           ܐ</foreign>
                </title>
                <finalRubric xml:lang="syr">ܫܠ̣ܡܘ ܢܘܼܗܳܪ̈ܐ ܕܢܨܚ̈ܢܐ ܕܦܠܓܘܼܬܐ ܩܕܡܝܬܐ
                              ܕܦܪܕܝܣܐ<locus from="12b"/>
                </finalRubric>
                <note>imperfect at the beginning.</note>
              </msItem>
              
              <msItem xml:id="b2" n="3">
                <locus from="12b" to="38">Foll. 12b-38</locus>
                <title xml:lang="en">Part second, sections <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܣܗ ـــ
                              ܠܕ</foreign>
                </title>
                <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܬܘܒ ܢܘܗܳܪ̈ܐ ܕܢܨ̈ܚܢܐ ܕܦܠܓܘܼܬܐ ܕܬܪ̈ܬܝܢ</rubric>
                <finalRubric xml:lang="syr">ܫܠܡ̣ܘ ܢܘܗܳܪ̈ܐ ܕܦܠܓܘܼܬܐ ܕܬܪ̈ܬܝܢ ܕܦܠܕܝܣ
                  <locus from="38b"/>
                </finalRubric>
              </msItem>
              
              <msItem xml:id="b3" n="4">
                <locus from="38b" to="65">Foll. 38b-65</locus>
                <title xml:lang="en">Part third, sections <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܩܚ ـــ
                              ܣܘ</foreign>.</title>
                <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܬܘܒ ܢܘܗܪ̈ܐ ܕܢܨ̈ܚܢܐ ܕܐܒ̈ܗܬܐ ܕܟܬܝ̣ܒܝܢ
                           ܠܐܝܪܴܢܴܘܡܻܝܣ</rubric>
                <finalRubric xml:lang="syr">ܫܠܡ ܢܘܗܳܪ̈ܐ ܕܢܨ̈ܚܢܐ ܕܐܒܗ̈ܬܐ ܕܟܬܝ̣ܒܝܢ ܒܟ̣ܬܒܐ ܕܦܪܕܝܣܐ:
                  ܒܬܠ̈ܬ ܦܠ̈ܓܘܢ ܬܪ̈ܬܝܢ ܕܦܠܕܝܣ: ܘܚܕܐ ܕܐܝܪܢܘܡܝܣ ܕܥܒ̣ܝܕ ܒܫ̈ܘܐܠܐ ܘܦܘܼܢܝ ܦܬܓ̈ܡܐ ܠܛܘܒ̣ܢܐ
                  ܡܪܝ ܩܛܪܝܐ ܕܡܢ ܥܘܼܡܪܐ ܕܒܨ̈ܠܘܬܗ ܘܒܨ̈ܠܘܬܐ ܕܟܠܗܘܢ ܩܕ̈ܝܫ܏ܘ ܕܡܪܢ ܢܬ݂ܢܛܪ ܟܢܘܫ̣ܝܐ ܟܠܗ
                  ܕܥܕܬܐ ܏ܩܕ ܡܢ ܟܠ ܢܟܝ̈ܢܝܢ. ܘܩܪܒܗ ܕܣܛܢܐ. ܘܐܡ̣ܝܢ
                  <!--How do we format the blanks here without making it look odd-->
                  <locus from="65a"/>
                </finalRubric>
                <note>The translation of the subscriptions provided by <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/807">Wright</persName>: "Here end the
                           Illustrations of the noble deeds of the Fathers, which were written in
                           the book of the Paradise in three parts, two by
                           <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/668">Palladius</persName> and one by
                           <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/857">Hieronymus</persName>,— composed in the form of questions and
                  answers by the <persName>blessed Mar — the Bactrian</persName>, from the convent of — , through whose prayers and those of all the Saints of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2245">our Lord</persName>, etc."</note>
              </msItem>
              
              <msItem xml:id="b4" n="5" defective="true">
                <locus from="65b" to="142"/>
                <title xml:lang="en">Part fourth, sections <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܦܗ ـــ
                              ܐ</foreign>
                </title>
                <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܥܠ ܚ̇ܝ̣ܠܗ ܕܡܪܢ ܝܫܘܥ ܡܫܝܚܐ: ܡܫܪܝܢܢ ܠܡܟܬ݂ܒ ܢܘܗܵܪܐ
                           ܕܫ̈ܘܠܐ ܕܦܠܓܘܬܐ ܐܚܪܳܝܬܐ ܕܟܬܒܐ ܕܦܪܕܝܣܐ܇ [ܕܥܒ̣ܝܕܐ ܠܦܠܕܝܘܣ.] ܕܐܝܬܝܗ̇ ܫܘܐܠܐ
                           ܕܐܚ̈ܐ: ܘܝܘܠܦܢܐ ܕܣ̈ܒܐ܀.</rubric>
                <note>imperfect at the end (see <bibl>Add. 17,263<ptr target="https://bl.syriac.uk/ms/1079"/>)
                  </bibl>.</note>
              </msItem>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
          
          <physDesc>
            <p>Paper, about 8 1/2 in. by 5 5/8, consisting of 142 leaves, many of which are much stained and torn, especially foll. 1, 2, 115, 116, and 122—142. The quires, signed with letters, were at least 17 in number; but the first two are lost, and <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܓ</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܝܙ</foreign> are imperfect. Four leaves are also missing after fol. 39. There are from 18 to 25 lines in each page. </p>
            <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                <extent>
                  <measure type="composition" unit="leaf" quantity="142">142 ff.</measure>
                </extent>
                        <condition>
                           <list>
                              <item>
                                 <p>Paper, about 8 1/2 in. by 5 5/8, consisting of 142 leaves, many
                                    of which are much stained and torn, especially foll. 1, 2, 115,
                                    116, and 122—142. The quires, signed with letters, were at least
                                    17 in number; but the first two are lost, and
                                       <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܓ</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܝܙ</foreign> are imperfect.
                                    Four leaves are also missing after fol. 39. There are from 18 to
                                    25 lines in each page. </p>
                              </item>
                           </list>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
            <handDesc hands="1">
              <handNote xml:id="handNote1" medium="unknown" scope="major" script="syr">
                This manuscript is written in a good hand of the <date calendar="Gregorian" notBefore="1200" notAfter="1300">xiiith cent.</date>, with
                           numerous Greek vowels and other points.</handNote>
            </handDesc>
            <additions>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <locus from="65a"/>
                  <p>With reference to the blanks we read on the margin (on part three, on fol.
                    65a): "These names were rubbed out. By thy life, O reader, if a copy falls into
                    thy hands, supply them, that thou mayest be forgiven." 
                    We should probably supply the names of <persName>ʾAnān-Yeshūaʿ</persName>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܥܢܢܝܫܘܥ</foreign>, and of the <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/223">convent of Beth-ʾAbē</placeName>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܒܶܝܬ
                      ܥܳܒܷ̈ܐ</foreign>.</p>
              
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
